## 🔥 Currently Open / Active Positions

### 1. University of Florida — GATOR Lab (GeoAI)
| Detail | Info |
|---|---|
| **Position** | 2× Fully Funded PhD Students |
| **Start** | Fall 2026 |
| **Status** | ✅ **OPEN — Rolling review** |
| **Research Areas** | (1) GeoAI & Scalable Analytics — cloud-native workflows, LLMs for geospatial reasoning; (2) Climate Resilience & Coastal Informatics — sea-level rise modeling |
| **Requirements** | Master's degree in GIScience, CS, Statistics, Data Science, or Geography; research track record |
| **Funding** | Full tuition waiver + stipend + health insurance |
| **How to Apply** | Email Dr. Levente Juhász at `join@gatorlab.io` with CV, GitHub link, and a brief "Why GATOR Lab" statement |
| **Website** | [gatorlab.io](https://gatorlab.io) |

> [!TIP]
> This is one of the strongest current opportunities for someone with GeoAI and remote sensing skills. They explicitly welcome original research proposals. Your precision agriculture + GeoAI background is a strong fit.

