## 🇺🇸 U.S. Federal Agency Fellowships

### NASA — FINESST (Future Investigators in NASA Earth and Space Science and Technology)
| Detail | Info |
|---|---|
| **Award** | Up to $50,000/yr for up to 3 years |
| **Eligibility** | U.S. citizens/permanent residents enrolled in PhD programs |
| **Focus** | Earth science, remote sensing, geospatial analysis |
| **Typical Deadline** | February–March annually |
| **Status** | Check [NSPIRES](https://nspires.nasaprs.com) for next solicitation |
| **Website** | [science.nasa.gov/researchers/sara/student-programs/finesst](https://science.nasa.gov/researchers/sara/student-programs/finesst/) |

### NSF — Graduate Research Fellowship Program (GRFP)
| Detail | Info |
|---|---|
| **Award** | $37,000/yr stipend + $16,000 cost-of-education allowance for 3 years |
| **Eligibility** | U.S. citizens/nationals/permanent residents; early-career grad students |
| **2026 Cycle** | ❌ Closed (deadline was ~November 2025) |
| **Next Cycle** | Expected ~October 2026 |
| **Website** | [nsf.gov/grfp](https://new.nsf.gov/funding/opportunities/nsf-graduate-research-fellowship-program-grfp) |

> [!WARNING]
> NSF GRFP is limited to U.S. citizens and permanent residents. If you are an international student, skip this and focus on the alternatives below.

